text:
‘Sculpture by the Sea’ returns to Bondi Beach to Tamarama Beach coastal walk Published on : Friday, October 23, 2015
Sculpture by the Sea returns to the Bondi Beach to Tamarama Beach coastal walk. This is the 17th edition of the event.
See the spectacular Bondi to Tamarama coastal walk transformed into a 2km long temporary sculpture park featuring over 100 sculptures by artists from Australia and across the world.
This event is free to the public.
This year the organisers of the event received 263 submissions, from 31 countries around the world, including Australia.
Hyundai will be the major exhibition partner for the fifth year. Hyundai will provide their popular complimentary chauffeur service for visitors to the exhibition. The Hyundai Santa Fe SUV Fleet, featuring the all-new Tuscon and Santa Fe, will operate on Saturdays and Sundays during the exhibition from 10am-5pm.
‘Sculpture by the Sea’ will be held from Oct 22- Nov 8.
